Moodle Group 1 Qs

Braden Baker

3/24/2021

Question 1: How Long Does it Take for Students to View Their Feedback

Most students viewed their feedback within a couple days but every class had outliers where a student would not view their feedback for days. This data also does not include students that never checked their feedback.

Generally, 80% of the time it can be expected that a student will view their feedback within about 50 hours from the time their feedback was posted.

Looking at the median time to view feedback to lessen the impact of the outliers, the time to view feedback in most classes drops to under 20 hours.

Question 2: Which Moodle Resources get the Most and Least Number of Interactions

An assignment module received the most views as expected. The next highest view was files which also had the highest number of modules added so its high view count is expected.

The viewership of URL is surprising since it had a large number of modules added. The other module types having low viewership is expected given their lower number of modules to viewed.

When looking at views per module, glossary is clearly at the top. Only one glossary modules was posted in the sample of logs but 450 views is very high and suggests it was used by students frequently. The choice model was similar, it was only used in one course by received quite a view views.

Students viewed most non assignment modules 1-2 times with the exception of choices, folders, and quizzes.

How to read, assignment received an average of 103 views per module added, each student viewed an assignment module on average 7 times, and each class had an average of 10 assignment modules added

How Often are Students Viewing Recorded Lectures?

Only one class in the sample of logs posted recorded lectures consistently so this is a small sample size. Viewership mostly has stayed the same throughout semester, between 3-9 views per student

ggplot(q31, aes(x=Date, y=Views)) + 
  geom_col(fill = "#2438f0") +
  theme_clean() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 10)) +
  labs(Title = "Distrubtion of views For Each Recorded Lecture",
       X = "Date Recording Posted",
       y = "Number of Views")

Most students viewed a recorded lecture within 5 days of a recording being posted. However another decently sized group viewed the recording lecture 13+ days after posting.

Examining further, it does seem that their may be two groups of views for recording lectures. One group views a few days after a recording is posted likely for homework, missing the class, or just going over it again. A second group viewes the recorded lecture days after it was posted likely for test preperation. This trend is strongest in November. Most November lectures received more views than other months later than the normal 5 days suggesting that the views may have been for prepared for end of semester exams or finals.
